{
  "stem": "10862.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They took us by train, and this is where I remember the German Shepherds.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The SS came, and they took us out.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were on the train for overnight.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I remember it was night time, and we finally arrived there in the morning, the following morning.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a boxcars, close, where they take cattle.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I remember one day that the train had to stop probably to change probably men, you know, the workers, and they did open the doors.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They opened the boxcar, and it was a beautiful-- it was in the summer time too-- it was a gorgeous day.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The sun was shining.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The fields were beautifully green, and the Polish people were looking at us at the train and making faces and yelling dirty names at us.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Nobody came to our rescue, nobody.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Instead of them giving us water or giving us food, they were standing and mocking us and yelling names at us.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I remember the SS standing with the German Shepherds, with their dogs, and then they finally closed the doors up again.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we arrived to Czestochowa, and they separated the men and the women and the 11 children that were finally left.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I was there among the children.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I was the oldest.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "At that time I think I was already 11-- yeah, 11 years old.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I was holding a six-month-old little baby that had-- that actually was born in the camp in Demblin.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the German looked at me, and he told me in German [GERMAN], throw the child away.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And, of course, I didn't want to throw the child away, so what I did I put the child down.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I noticed that all the women were, were being disrobed.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They had to throw away the old uniforms.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
